            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "When I first reported this my understanding wasn't complete, the actual issue here is resizing with large horizontal output it seems. Here's a functional test that reliably reproduces this issue. I'm going to see if I can spend some time over the next few days trying find the issue here.\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/8541a0839a16b52b714328b35ebdc437dd6d9b36\n\n```\n  it('does not crash on zoomout with large output #30374', function()\n    skip(is_os('win'))\n\n    feed([[:terminal<cr>]])\n    -- Start terminal smaller.\n    screen:try_resize(100, 100)\n    command('call jobresize(b:terminal_job_id, 100, 100)')\n\n    -- Generate very wide output.\n    feed(\"ifor i in $(seq 1 1000); do echo -n $i; done\\r\\n\")\n\n    -- Make terminal big.\n    screen:try_resize(2000, 2000)\n    command('call jobresize(b:terminal_job_id, 2000, 2000)')\n\n    assert_alive()\n  end)\n```",
